OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1783639966
OL,3,CDisability benefits not fit for
OL,4,Cpurpose and need bold reform, says Pip
OL,5,Creview
OL,7,FIt follows a climbdown from Starmer's
OL,8,Fgovernment in June last year, when it
OL,9,FU-turned on proposed cuts to
OL,10,Fdisability benefits, in a bid to avoid
OL,11,Fa rebellion from Labour's backbenches.
OL,13,FPip is intended to help with everyday
OL,14,Ftasks and extra living costs if
OL,15,Fsomeone has a long-term physical or
OL,16,Fmental health condition or disability.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,320,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1783639966
OL,3,CDisability benefits not fit for
OL,4,Cpurpose and need bold reform, says Pip
OL,5,Creview
OL,7,FThe latest official figures, released
OL,8,Fearlier this year, showed the number
OL,9,Fof people in England and Wales
OL,10,Fclaiming the main disability benefit
OL,11,Fpassed four million for the first time
OL,12,F` roughly doubling since 2019.
OL,14,FThe number of claimants classed as
OL,15,Fhaving autistic spectrum disorders has
OL,16,Fmore than doubled in six years,
OL,17,Faccording to Press Association
OL,18,Fanalysis, as has the number with mixed
OL,19,Fanxiety and depressive disorders,
OL,20,Fwhile the number with ADHD has almost
OL,21,Fquadrupled in that time period.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,320,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1783639966
OL,3,CDisability benefits not fit for
OL,4,Cpurpose and need bold reform, says Pip
OL,5,Creview
OL,7,FThe report has revealed that while Pip
OL,8,Fis widely valued as a cash benefit, it
OL,9,Fis not working as intended for
OL,10,Fdisabled people or wider society.
OL,12,FWhile many disabled people say Pip is
OL,13,Fvital in helping them meet the extra
OL,14,Fcosts of disability and participate in
OL,15,Feveryday life, others state Pip
OL,16,Fcreates barriers to participating
OL,17,Ffully in work, social and community
OL,18,Flife. This is particularly true for
OL,19,Fpeople with fluctuating conditions,
OL,20,Fless visible conditions or multiple
OL,21,Fconditions.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,320,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31906
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1783639966
OL,3,CDisability benefits not fit for
OL,4,Cpurpose and need bold reform, says Pip
OL,5,Creview
OL,7,FClaimants of Pip, reported often
OL,8,Ffinding the system to apply for the
OL,9,Fbenefit "dehumanising", "soul-
OL,10,Fdestroying", and "degrading", with 90%
OL,11,Fof respondents viewing the process
OL,12,F"negatively" according to the report.
OL,14,FIt also found low levels of trust in
OL,15,Fthe system and the need for it to be
OL,16,Frebuilt, both for disabled people and
OL,17,Fthose with long-term conditions, as
OL,18,Fwell as for the taxpayer.
OL,26,@qD@IOUqD@VO]qD@YOUrD@KO]rD@ROUrD@\O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,320,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31907
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1783639966
OL,3,CDisability benefits not fit for
OL,4,Cpurpose and need bold reform, says Pip
OL,5,Creview
OL,7,FIt noted that while Pip "enables many
OL,8,Fpeople to stay in work" through
OL,9,Fcovering extra costs of disability,
OL,10,Fthere is research that "demonstrates
OL,11,Fthat some people on Pip are scared to
OL,12,Fparticipate, either in physical
OL,13,Factivities or employment, as this
OL,14,Fcould be seen as evidence that their
OL,15,Ffunctional ability has improved".
OL,26,@oD@YOUpD@WO]rD@XOUwD@`O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,320,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31908
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1783639966
OL,3,CDisability benefits not fit for
OL,4,Cpurpose and need bold reform, says Pip
OL,5,Creview
OL,7,FSpeaking to journalists on Thursday,
OL,8,FSir Stephen Timms said the review was
OL,9,Fabout ensuring the system was "fit and
OL,10,Ffair" for future generations,
OL,11,Fpromising recommendations for reform
OL,12,Fwhen the full report is published in
OL,13,Fthe Autumn.
OL,15,F"We want to make sure that Pip is fair
OL,16,Fand fit for the future," said Stephen
OL,17,FTimms
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
